Mexico’s Marcatel Acquires 50% of STX Communications in U.S.

-- B y   A d r i a n a   L o p e z   C a r a v e o
-- 
2011-07-15T14:17:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-15/mexico-s-marcatel-acquires-50-of-stx-communications-in-u-s-.html
Marcatel SA , a closely held Mexican
telecommunications company, bought a 50 percent of stake of STX
Communications, the largest distributor of phone cards in U.S.,
the company said today in an e-mail statement distributed by
PRNewswire.  Marcatel aims to strength its business structure through
STX Communications, a  New York  based company, according to the
statement. The company didn’t disclosed the financial terms of
the transaction.  The Monterrey-based Marcatel was created thirteen years ago
and has more than 600 workers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adriana Lopez Caraveo in Mexico City at 
 adrianalopez@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jose Enrique Arrioja in Mexico City at 
 jarrioja@bloomberg.net  